Higher median income

Median income is positively correlated with the number of litter bins in Manhattan

This map shows how the total number of litter baskets and median income vary together by Manhattan community district. Green areas have both a high median income and number of litter baskets, while pale blue areas have a relatively low median income and number of litter baskets.

Higher number of litter bins

In Community Board 9, the median income is $55,726 (44.4 percent lower than the Manhattan median income of $100,273).

The district has 464 litter bins (40.5 percent lower than the Manhattan district average of 780 bins).

In Community Board 5, the median income is $141,722 (41.3 percent higher than the Manhattan median income of $100,273). The district has 1141 litter bins (46.2 percent higher than the Manhattan district average of 780 bins).

Source: NYC Open Data, 2016-2020 American Community Survey.

Litter bin data from 2022. Median income data from 2016-2020.

Graphic by Adina Cazacu-De Luca
